ons?f_ri=1275778"}, {"id": 991343, "name": "Muslim Students", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Muslim_Students?f_ri=1275778"}, {"id": 1275778, "name": "Muslims In Thailand", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Muslims_In_Thailand?f_ri=1275778"}, {"id": 1375815, "name": "Patani", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Patani?f_ri=1275778"}, {"id": 1383357, "name": "Pattani", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/Pattani?f_ri=1275778"}, {"id": 2701629, "name": "History of Ayutthaya", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/Documents/in/History_of_Ayutthaya?f_ri=1275778"}]}, {"id": 40635563, "title": "Defining Human, Defining Thai The Identity Crisis Exhibited by the 2015 Constitution Draft Process and Tourism Industry in Thailand", "created_at": "2019-10-16T00:52:52.750-07:00", "url": "https://www.academia.edu/40635563/Defining_Human_Defining_Thai_The_Identity_Crisis_Exhibited_by_the_2015_Constitution_Draft_Process_and_Tourism_Industry_in_Thailand?f_ri=1275778", "dom_id": "work_40635563", "summary": "In May of 2014, the Chief Commander of the Royal Thai Army, Prayuth Chan-o-cha, executed a coup to depose former Prime Minister Yingluck Shinawatra and the governing Pheu Thai Party.  Shortly thereafter, the military junta enacted interim constitutional law, suspending the 2007 Constitution to sanction the authority of Prayuth\u2019s National Council for Peace and Order (NCPO). This paper deals with the fallout of the 23rd attempt at re-writing the Thai constitution in less than two centuries, and how it has affected Thailand's sense of national identity, including both the Buddhist majority and Muslim minority. This paper also investigates the nuanced impact that Western tourism has had on a nation that was never colonized, and how that has changed the economic makeup of the country and foreign policy objectives of the new government.", "downloadable_attachments": [{"id": 60916618, "asset_id": 40635563, "asset_type": "Work", "always_allow_d